  "timeframe": "Weekly / 4H / 15m",
  "market_context": "GBP/JPY weekly chart had just swept an old high (external range liquidity) and was retracing into a weekly fair value gap (internal range liquidity), with a new external range liquidity target above. The analyst dropped down to the 4-hour to frame a market maker model transition.",
  "key_observation": "Price delivers cyclically from external to internal range liquidity, then back to external. The weekly retracement into the FVG paired with a 4-hour sell-to-buy model transition (CISD over the swing high) frames an entry targeting the next external liquidity pool.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the weekly, identify the old high taken out as external range liquidity and mark the weekly fair value gap below as internal range liquidity.",
    "Step 2: Project the next external range liquidity above for the continuation up after internal liquidity is filled.",
    "Step 3: Drop to the 4-hour chart, where the same weekly FVG appears as old lows; observe displacement down into internal liquidity (weekly FVG).",
    "Step 4: Wait for price to change the state of delivery by closing above a 4-hour swing high, transitioning from a sell model to a buy model.",
    "Step 5: Within the 4-hour buy leg, identify a new 4-hour fair value gap as internal range liquidity and the old high above as external range liquidity.",
    "Step 6: Drop to the 15-minute chart, see consolidation on the 4-hour FVG, a sweep below, and a change in state of delivery forming an order block entry.",
    "Step 7: Enter at the 15-minute order block with stop on the swept low; target 4-hour external range liquidity with runners to the weekly external range liquidity (old high)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade triggered, target hit with an aggressive move higher; runners reached the weekly external range liquidity (old high).",
  "lessons": "Nesting the internal/external range liquidity cycle across multiple time frames (weekly → 4-hour → 15-minute) allows a market maker buy model to be framed within a larger market maker buy model, providing precise entries with high R potential.",
